& [SLMLexicalSubstrateDeltaRebuildWorkflowContract] is the contract for repeatable lexical substrate rebuilds
  + [contract_uuid] is f83fd3c1-8377-4b0a-a135-764d19b2eec9
  + [slice_id] is SLM-52
  + [depends_on] is SLM_Lexical_Authority_Foundation_Contract, SLM_Source_Only_Verification_Gate_Contract
  + [status] is verified_source_gate

  & [Purpose] is to make lexical database and substrate pack rebuilds explicit and auditable
    = must: preserve downloaded source documents separately from generated artifacts
    = must: show rebuild commands before executing them
    = must: report current artifact checksums
    = must: default to dry-run
    = must: require an explicit flag before source download or local artifact regeneration
    - never: silently overwrite raw source documents

  & [WorkflowSteps] are the planned rebuild sequence
    + [step] is optional download_open_english_wordnet.py
    + [step] is build_lexicon_db.py
    + [step] is export_lexicon_cache.py
    + [step] is build_lexical_substrate_pack.py
    + [step] is slm_source_gate_check.py

  & [RuntimeProjection] is the source surface
    + [script] is slm_lexicon/scripts/rebuild_lexical_substrate_workflow.py
    + [documentation] is slm_lexicon/REBUILD_WORKFLOW.sop
    + [proof_route] is dry-run plus source gate

  ! [Slice52SourceComplete] is accepted
    @ [dry_run] passed python slm_lexicon/scripts/rebuild_lexical_substrate_workflow.py --dry-run
    @ [source_gate] passed python slm_project/tools/slm_source_gate_check.py
    @ [python_compile] source gate now compiles 7 Python scripts
    @ [checksum_reporting] printed raw manifest, SQLite, substrate manifest, index, closed-class table, and source provenance sha256 values
